[Black "Chapter 3 Scheveningen Formation II"]

{In Chapters 2 and 3, Black establishes the modest e6/d6 central pawn duo that resembles the Scheveningen structure, one of Black's most solid and flexible defensive systems in the Open Sicilian.}

1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 dxc3 4. Nxc3 Nc6 5. Nf3 d6 6. Bc4 e6 7. O-O Be7 8. Qe2 a6 {[%entry]} 9. Rd1 Qc7 10. Bf4 Nf6 (10... Ne5? 11. Bxe5 dxe5 12. Bb5+ axb5 13. Nxb5 Qb6 14. Nxe5 Nf6 15. Nc4) 11. Rac1 O-O 12. Bb3 Qb8 (12... Rd8 13. Nd5 exd5 14. exd5) (12... Nh5 13. Be3) 13. e5 Nh5 14. Bg5 dxe5 15. Bxe7 *
